<p>Involvement of the Notch signaling pathway during endocrine cell differentiation. The Notch ligand Delta is first up-regulated in differentiating endocrine cells. It binds to Notch on neighboring non-endocrine cells, which results in release of the Notch intracellular domain (Notch IC). Notch IC translocates into the nucleus and interacts with RBP-Jκ to activate target genes such as Hes1. Hes1 then inhibits proendocrine bHLH transcription factors such as Ngn3.</p>
